&lt;p&gt;Location: Pathology, Cross Site&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job Title: Medical Examiner Officer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band: 6&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours: 37.5&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Contract Type: Disclosure Check: Enhanced&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;*&lt;strong&gt;Please note this post will be closed early once a sufficient amount of applications have been received&lt;/strong&gt;*&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity exists for two suitably qualified Medical Examiner Officers to join the newly created Medical Examiner Service within the Pathology department at North Tees and Hartlepool NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Medical Examiner Service, comprising of Medical Examiners, Medical Examiner Officers and Bereavement Support Officers use their combined skills and compassion to deliver a high quality service for the deceased and bereaved.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Medical Examiner Officer is expected to support the Medical Examiner in scrutinising the circumstances and causes of death.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition, you will be a point of contact and source of advice for relatives of deceased patients, healthcare professionals and coroner and registration services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The nature of the job is such that it demands high standards of integrity. It is essential that you have good interpersonal skills with the ability to show empathy and deal sensitively with bereaved families&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome applications from candidates educated to Batchelor’s degree level, or evidence of study/equivalent practical experience at an advanced level; this might include nursing and/or other clinical experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note, candidates must have completed the mandatory e-learning MEO core training modules (free of charge) prior to starting in the post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full time position which currently operates Monday to Friday. NB may be subject to change as the service develops&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSharron PooleyJob titlePathology Services ManagerEmail addresssharron.pooley@nhs.netTelephone number01642 624448Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
